  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://semanticweb.iiitb.ac.in/iiitb/lab_Intervention_Dashboard_Maternal_Deaths">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://semanticweb.iiitb.ac.in/edu#Lab"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">Intervention Dashboard – Maternal Deaths</rdfs:label>
    <edu:name rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Intervention Dashboard – Maternal Deaths</edu:name>
    <edu:url rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI">https://wsl.iiitb.ac.in/intervention-dashboard-maternal-deaths/</edu:url>
    <edu:category rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">lab_wsl</edu:category>
    <edu:scrapedAt rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">2026-03-26T19:08:19</edu:scrapedAt>
    <edu:description rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">There are 4 components to the below dashboard. In Predictive Impact Analysis dashboard, we can see the impact of different factors on Maternal Deaths (MD). We can intervene on a factor by selecting it from the dropdown menu and change it by any amount (eg: +10% , -10% etc) and we can see the corresponding changes in MD at district level. In Prescriptive modelling dashboard, we can set the target MD and the model outputs the prescribed values of different factors in order to achieve the specified target MD. We can also see the corresponding change in MD at the district level by adopting these prescribed values of the factor. We can also see sensitivities of different factors which talks about the importance of the factor and it ranges from 0 to 1. If a domain expert deems a specific factor</edu:description>
    <edu:belongsTo rdf:resource="http://semanticweb.iiitb.ac.in/iiitb/IIIT_Bangalore"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://semanticweb.iiitb.ac.in/iiitb/faculty_dr_vinu_e_venugopal">
