  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://semanticweb.iiitb.ac.in/iiitb/governance_Balakrishnan_Ashok">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://semanticweb.iiitb.ac.in/edu#GovernanceMember"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">Balakrishnan Ashok</rdfs:label>
    <edu:name rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Balakrishnan Ashok</edu:name>
    <edu:url rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI">https://www.iiitb.ac.in/administration/balakrishnan-ashok</edu:url>
    <edu:bio rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Education : Ph.D. (University of Massachusetts Amherst) Postdoctoral work at the Lorentz Institute for Theoretical Physics, Leiden, The Netherlands, and at the Materials Research Centre, Indian Institute of Science, Bangalore. Prior to joining IIITB in July, 2012, he was an Assistant Professor at the Central University of Hyderabad since April, 2007. Complex Systems, Nonlinear dynamics, Biomechanics &amp; Biology-motivated problems, Theoretical Soft Condensed Matter  &amp; Polymer Physics Know more: Complex Systems &amp; Soft Matter Physics Lab Teaching Experience in the recent past: Core courses: Courses taught earlier: At the University of Hyderabad, Hyderabad (April, 2007 - May, 2012): Research interests: Our research interests focus on the study of complex systems and soft matter physics. This involves the modelling of various physical &amp; biological systems, using dynamical systems theory and methods. These include biomechanics (the dynamics and control of vesicular nanotubulation), diverse com</edu:bio>
    <edu:scrapedAt rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">2026-03-26T19:08:33</edu:scrapedAt>
    <edu:governs rdf:resource="http://semanticweb.iiitb.ac.in/iiitb/IIIT_Bangalore"/>
  </rdf:Description>
