    <edu:body rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">The consultation, “Re-imagining Pathways for Assistive Technology,” will be a significant step towards creating an inclusive and vibrant AT ecosystem in
India. CAGS hosted a team of students and faculties from the New York University’s Centre for Global Affairs on 15th January 2025 An online Summer School organised by the Centre for Accessibility in the Global South (CAGS), IIIT Bangalore 3:00 pm – 5:00 pm from 24th to 28th June 2024 (Register HERE) Int In association with Samarthanam Trust for the Disabled, the Centre for Accessibility in the Global South (CAGS) at IIIT Bangalore organized a</edu:body>
    <edu:scrapedAt rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">2026-03-26T19:07:37</edu:scrapedAt>
    <edu:belongsTo rdf:resource="http://semanticweb.iiitb.ac.in/iiitb/IIIT_Bangalore"/>
  </rdf:Description>
